  "title": "Legal Executive",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Roles and Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Assist in the preparation and drafting of legal documents, including finance documents, security documents, corporate authorities, legal opinions, and agreements</li></ul><ul><li>Support transactional work, including pre-closing, closing, and post-closing matters, as well asconditions precedent and subsequent</li></ul><ul><li>Assist with client onboarding, including KYC checks and matter file opening</li></ul><ul><li>Liaise with clients, government authorities, and corresponding counsel where required</li></ul><ul><li>Attend meetings and closings (physical and remote)</li></ul><ul><li>Conduct research and provide support to both corporate and litigation teams as required</li></ul><ul><li>Maintain accurate records and tracking of application deadlines, submissions, and approvals</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Degree from a recognised university</li><li>Preferably with relevant experience</li><li>Proficiency in writing and communication of English</li><li>Proficiency in MSWord, MSExcel, MSPowerpoint and MSOutlook Software applications</li><li>Good organisational and administration skills</li><li>Attention to detail and problem-solving abilities</li><li>Ability to work independently and under pressure in fast-paced environment</li><li>Ability to audio type (receiving dictation) will be a big plus</li></ul><p>How to Apply:</p><p>Submit your resume and cover letter to <a href=\"mailto:Recruitment@incisivelaw.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Recruitment@incisivelaw.com</a>. Only shortlisted will be contacted.    </p>",
